It scratches all the itches. Great closure movie but still leaves enough open for future movies. Some closure I wish hadn't happened because it would have been great to see things develop more in future movies, but its Star Wars, I guess anything could happen.
I enjoyed the Episode 9! People who like it or love it have their reasons and for those who don't are right as well. I thought it was great and highly recommended it if you're a fan.
Nice ending to an iconic saga.
Excellent conclusion to a story I have loved since I was a kid. Haters will hate, but I loved it/

To me, this was the perfect conclusion to the Skywalker Saga. The movie was not perfect, but when Star Wars came out it was fast past, fun, joyful, and kept you on the edge of your seat. This is what TROS did for me. Many of the storylines from TLJ still made it through but after a year, our characters have learned different perspectives about those events. Thanks JJ for reeling this in and give us a fun last adventure with the Skywalker Saga!!!

I'm a star wars fiend, have been since the first movies. I have to say that the only downside is this felt kind of like 2 movies crammed into one and should have probably been given a little more running time to work it all in there, but other than that, they did an excellent job trying to bring all the threads of this last trilogy together. I rather enjoyed the whole adventure, which is more than I can say for some of the absurdities in the last movie.
I didn't love it, but I didn't hate it. I just think it could have been better.
Leave the nitpicking for much later when you need a few good laughs, just go in and enjoy all the fan service!
